# Deploy to Cloudflare reads this file to render a pre-labeled secret field
# in the deploy form (users paste only the value), and `wrangler dev` uses a
# copy of it (as .dev.vars) for local development.
#
# DOCSDEV_SITE_TOKEN — the site token (dst_…) from your app.docs.dev
# dashboard card. It binds this deployment to your team on first boot and
# stays with the Worker (as a secret) so custom domains you add later can
# request approval automatically. Connecting later from /admin instead?
# Enter: unset
DOCSDEV_SITE_TOKEN=
